<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The controlling expression is 'err' in 'if (err)'. 'err' is initialized from the macro LFS_LOCK(lfs->cfg), which is defined as ((void)cfg,0) — a comma expression that always yields the constant 0. Therefore the if condition is invariantly false (never taken), violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.3 (controlling expressions shall not be invariant).
</scenario>
